				\begin{document}$${\text{P}}_{\text{G}} = 1 - (1 - {\text{P}}_{\text{C}} )^{{{ 1\mathord{\left/ {\vphantom { 1{\text{r}}}} \right. \kern-0pt} {\text{r}}}}} ,$$\end{document}PG=1-(1-PC)1r,where r is the ratio of the length of a specific chromosome to the length of the genome considered for QTL detection as in Tilquin et al. [16]. Confidence intervals for QTL (95 %) were estimated using the LOD drop-off method as proposed by Lander and Botstein [15].
